    This is the interface of Card.

    This is the interface of the Freecell model.

    This is the interface of the FreecellOperationsBuilder.

    This is the interface of ICardValue.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CardImpl
    This class implements the interface Card and provides the methods specific to a card.
    A card should have a suit and value.
    It has a constructor that takes a card's suit as CardSuit which is an enum, and card's value as ICardValue which is another enum and creates a card.
    A card with only the values in enums can be created.
    FreecellModel
    This class implements the interface FreecellOperations and provides the methods to be performed in a Freecell game.
    A freecell game play is divided among three types of card piles.
    This class has a private constructor with integer parameters cascade, open, foundation for the three piles in the game.
    Foundation pile
    These four piles are initially empty, and the goal of Freecell is to collect all cards of all suits in their respective foundation piles.
    FreecellModel.FreecellOperationsBuilderImpl
    Builder class which returns the instance of FreecellModel class.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CardSuit
    Suits for the four types of cards in the game of Freecell.
    CardValue
    Value for the 13 types of values of cards in the game of Freecell.
    FreecellState
    States for a particular Freecell game.
    PileType
    Type for the three types of piles in a game of Freecell.
